premise_source_doc_sentence: Michael David Rapaport  (  born March 20 , 1970  )  is an American actor , podcast host , director and comedian .
He has acted in more than forty films since the early 1990s .
His best known roles on television are Boston Public , Friends , The War at Home , Prison Break , and Justified .

Some of his film roles include True Romance  (  1993  )  , Higher Learning  (  1995  )  , Cop Land  (  1997  )  , Deep Blue Sea  (  1999  )  , The 6th Day  (  2000  )  , Dr. Dolittle 2  (  2001  )  , Big Fan  (  2009  )  , and The Heat  (  2013  )  .

The Pallbearer is a 1996 American romantic comedy film co-written and directed by Matt Reeves and starring David Schwimmer , Gwyneth Paltrow , Toni Collette , Michael Vartan , Michael Rapaport , and Barbara Hershey .
The cast includes Elisabeth Moss , Ron Perlman , Naomi Watts , Jim Gaffigan , Michael Rapaport , Pooch Hall , Morgan Spector , Jason Jones , William Hill and Wass Stevens .
